<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.00/1157.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Commissioner</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Puerto
                                        Cortes</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-04"><hi rend="italic">March 4,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Dawson reports the receipt of a telegram of this date from Dávila
                            accepting the peace arrangement; that the President and Vice President
                            are expected to resign and that Congress will elect Bertrand as first
                            designate.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>